uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.serial

Class IInstanceRenderInput

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.serial.IInstanceRenderInput

  • public class IInstanceRenderInput
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the input-data for a specific IFrame/ISlot network rendering operation to be performed by a IInstanceRenderer, including structures into which certain output-data may be written.

      • setValuesUpdate

        public void setValuesUpdate(IValuesUpdate valuesUpdate)
        Registers the latest client-update operation prior to the network being rendered.

        NOTE: This information, if applicable, should be provided when sending information to the server for automatic-update.

        Parameters:
        valuesUpdate - Latest client-update operation

      • setFrameXDocIds

        public void setFrameXDocIds(java.util.Map<IFrame,java.lang.String> frameXDocIds)
        Sets the map of document-specific frame-identifiers to be used by the renderer, possibly fully or partially pre-populated. Identifiers will be generated and written into the map for any frames that are not represented in the initial version.
        Parameters:
        frameXDocIds - Map of frames to document-specific frame-identifiers, either fully or partially populated

      • getFrameXDocIds

        public java.util.Map<IFrame,java.lang.String> getFrameXDocIds()
        Provides the map that will contain the document-specific frame-identifiers used by the renderer. The identifiers can be either pre-provided via the setFrameXDocIds method, automatically generated by the renderer, or a mixture of both.
        Returns:
        Map of frames to document-specific frame-identifiers
